Plain
Nerijus Ramanauskas <nerijus@signaintermedia.com>


OVERVIEW

    Plain is a minimalist embeddable scripting language influenced by
    Tcl, Bash, and Lisp. It is a platform-independent library with no
    I/O of its own — all input/output is the host application's concern.

    The library provides:
        - Tokenization and tree walking (Plain.h)
        - A full runtime: variable frames, callables, built-in procedures,
          infix operators, control flow (VM.h)

    The host embeds it by supplying a PLAIN_CONTEXT, optionally handling
    unknown keywords via a callback, and calling PLAIN_EVALUATE.

    See Documentation/Syntax and Documentation/Semantics.


REQUIREMENTS

    xmake 2.5 or later. Get it at https://xmake.io

    Linux and macOS also require readline (for Inspector):

        Ubuntu/Debian:  apt install libreadline-dev
        Fedora/RHEL:    dnf install readline-devel
        macOS:          brew install readline


BUILD

    Build everything (library + Inspector):

        xmake

    Build only the library:

        xmake build plain

    Build only Inspector:

        xmake build inspector

    Run Inspector directly after building:

        xmake run inspector


OPTIONS

    Pass options with `xmake f` before building.

    --debugging=y    Enable debug assertions and symbols.
    --embedded=y     Build plain as a shared library instead of static.

    Examples:

        xmake f --debugging=y && xmake
        xmake f --embedded=y && xmake

    Reset options back to defaults:

        xmake f -c


PLATFORMS

    Tested configurations:

        Linux   x64, ARMv8
        macOS   x64
        Windows x64

    Inspector uses readline on Linux and macOS. On Windows it falls back
    to a plain fgets-based prompt with no history or line editing.


TARGETS

    plain        Static (or shared) library. Link against this to embed
                 Plain in any application: CLI, GUI, web server, game
                 engine, or anything else.

    inspector    Interactive REPL for experimenting with the language.


INCLUDE

    Include/Plain/Plain.h    Core parsing API: tokenizer, walker, types.
    Include/Plain/VM.h       Full runtime: PLAIN_EVALUATE, PLAIN_CONTEXT,
                             PLAIN_RESOLVE, PLAIN_CONTEXT_INIT, and everything
                             from Plain.h. This is the only header a host
                             application needs.
